Bellspine resonance entity clearance
-1 1 3 0 135 165 3440 8000 6 3800000 0
6184 6187 6188
Kowloon's Jade Magistracy holds surviving Conclave technical documents describing the Bellspine pass as a network of resonance-monitoring anchors built to track geological instability across the Ember Crown range. The constructs reactivated centuries ago and the area has been hostile territory since. Before the Magistracy can send documentation teams to assess what the anchors have been recording, field agents need to suppress the resonance entity population: resonance serpents attuned to the standing waves, crystal anchor shards that have gained hostile animate form, and resonance wraiths sustained by the chamber frequencies. Clear one of each.
Kowloon's documentation teams have entered the Bellspine pass and confirmed that the resonance entities have been cleared to a navigable level. Preliminary readings from intact anchor instruments show continuous seismic and geological data recording spanning approximately three centuries without interruption — a data archive that the Jade Magistracy is treating as one of the most significant Conclave research finds since the Black Ledger was sealed.
